.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/024-compact-code-graph/research/iterations/iteration-062.md:14:**Design implication**: The MCP server can detect "first call in a new session" by tracking whether a given ephemeral session ID has been seen before. Since non-hook runtimes never pass a sessionId, every call generates a new UUID. The server needs an in-memory timestamp map keyed by a higher-level identity (tenantId + userId + agentId hash, or a process-level singleton if no identity is available).
