.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-spec-kit-internals/003-template-levels/004-fix-template-deferred-followups/decision-record.md:135:## ADR-002: `parent_session_id` semantics
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-spec-kit-internals/003-template-levels/004-fix-template-deferred-followups/decision-record.md:147:Historical packets may omit session lineage or use `parent_session_id: null`. A strict existence requirement would break backward compatibility.
.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/002-spec-kit-internals/003-template-levels/004-fix-template-deferred-followups/decision-record.md:151:Use lenient semantics. `parent_session_id: null` is valid, and a non-null value that cannot be found emits warning code `SESSION_LINEAGE_BROKEN`.
