.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/z_archive/022-hybrid-rag-fusion/001-hybrid-rag-fusion-epic/scratch/agent-output-iter-013-codex-A1.md:8:4. `sessionId` is being used as an exact visibility filter, not just a personalization signal. Stage 1 folds `config.sessionId` into the governance scope and filters candidates with it ([stage1-candidate-gen.ts:494](\/Users\/michelkerkmeester\/MEGA\/Development\/Opencode Env\/Public\/.opencode\/skill\/system-spec-kit\/mcp_server\/lib\/search\/pipeline\/stage1-candidate-gen.ts#L494), [stage1-candidate-gen.ts:514](\/Users\/michelkerkmeester\/MEGA\/Development\/Opencode Env\/Public\/.opencode\/skill\/system-spec-kit\/mcp_server\/lib\/search\/pipeline\/stage1-candidate-gen.ts#L514)). The scope predicate requires exact `row.session_id === requested.sessionId` whenever a session id is present ([scope-governance.ts:360](\/Users\/michelkerkmeester\/MEGA\/Development\/Opencode Env\/Public\/.opencode\/skill\/system-spec-kit\/mcp_server\/lib\/governance\/scope-governance.ts#L360), [scope-governance.ts:461](\/Users\/michelkerkmeester\/MEGA\/Development\/Opencode Env\/Public\/.opencode\/skill\/system-spec-kit\/mcp_server\/lib\/governance\/scope-governance.ts#L461)). My inference: this likely over-narrows retrieval for normal sessioned searches by hiding tenant/user/global memories that should still be eligible and only boosted/deduped by session logic.
