     2	title: "Decision Record: §4.A — Fan-out executor dispatch strategy (packet 123)"
     3	description: "Resolves how each executor kind participates in fan-out: CLI kinds via headless subprocess pool, native via sequential YAML agent dispatches. All kinds supported; mixed configs work."
     4	trigger_phrases:
     5	  - "123 fanout executor dispatch"
     6	  - "fanout native dispatch decision"
     7	  - "4A executor fan-out strategy"
     8	importance_tier: "important"
     9	contextType: "decision"
    10	---
    11	<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: decision-record | v2.2 -->
    12	<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->
    13	
    14	# Decision Record: §4.A — Fan-out executor dispatch strategy
    15	
    16	---
    17	
    18	<!-- ANCHOR:adr-001 -->
    19	## ADR-001: Each executor kind uses its own native dispatch mechanism
    20	
    21	### Metadata
    22	
    23	| Field | Value |
    24	|-------|-------|
    25	| **Status** | Accepted |
    26	| **Date** | 2026-05-30 |
    27	| **Deciders** | User + Claude (packet 123 session 3) |
    28	
    29	---
    30	
    31	<!-- ANCHOR:adr-001-context -->
    32	### Context
    33	
    34	Fan-out runs N executor "lineages" in parallel, each converging independently in its own
    35	isolated sub-packet. The blocker: the deep-research/deep-review loop has no headless binary —
    36	it is agent/YAML-orchestrated. Specifically the `native` path in `step_dispatch_iteration`
    37	calls `agent: deep-research/deep-review`, which cannot run unattended in a subprocess pool.
    38	
    39	The user's requirement: every executor type (including `native`) must support fan-out using
    40	its OWN native sub-agent mechanism. Configs may mix types freely.
    41	<!-- /ANCHOR:adr-001-context -->
    42	
    43	---
    44	
    45	<!-- ANCHOR:adr-001-constraints -->
    46	### Constraints
    47	
    48	- Single-executor path must remain byte-identical (hard parity gate at Phase 6).
    49	- No new schema columns in `deep-loop-graph.sqlite` (triggers destructive migration).
    50	- Same-kind replicas must not collide on lockfiles (`SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR` isolation).
    51	- Comment hygiene: no spec-path or tracking-id labels in code comments.
    52	<!-- /ANCHOR:adr-001-constraints -->
    53	
    54	---
    55	
    56	<!-- ANCHOR:adr-001-decision -->
    57	### Decision
    58	
    59	**Each executor kind dispatches fan-out lineages via its own native mechanism:**
    60	
    61	| Kind | Fan-out mechanism | Parallelism |
    62	|------|-------------------|-------------|
    63	| `cli-codex` | `fanout-run.cjs` spawns N headless `codex exec` subprocesses, each running the full loop with `--artifact-dir-override` | True parallel (pool-capped) |
    64	| `cli-claude-code` | `fanout-run.cjs` spawns N headless `claude -p` subprocesses, each running the full loop | True parallel (pool-capped) |
    65	| `cli-opencode` / `cli-gemini` / `cli-devin` | Same pattern — pool-spawned subprocess per lineage | True parallel (pool-capped) |
    66	| `native` | YAML `step_fanout_spawn_native` dispatches N sequential `agent: deep-research/deep-review` runs with isolated dirs | Sequential (in-context, expected for count 1–3) |
    67	
    68	Mixed configs: CLI lineages run via `fanout-run.cjs` pool (background, headless); native
    69	lineages run as sequential YAML agent dispatches. The YAML `step_fanout_spawn` coordinates
    70	both tracks, then jumps directly to `phase_synthesis` (skipping `phase_init` / `phase_main_loop`).
    71	
    72	The key enabling mechanism for all types: `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir` override.
    73	When present in `step_resolve_artifact_root`, the loop binds `artifact_dir` to the override
    74	directly, writing to `{base_artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/` without touching other lineages.
    75	
    76	"Native codex sub-agents" = headless `codex exec` processes — each subprocess IS a native
    77	codex agent running the loop autonomously. "Native claude sub-agents" = headless `claude -p`
    78	processes. For `native`, the sub-agents are literal `@deep-research`/`@deep-review` agents.
    79	<!-- /ANCHOR:adr-001-decision -->
    80	
    81	---
    82	
    83	<!-- ANCHOR:adr-001-alternatives -->
    84	### Alternatives Considered
    85	
    86	**Option A (original §4.A plan):** Native stays single-executor only; parallel mode = CLI only.
    87	Rejected because the user requires native fan-out to work.
    88	
    89	**Option B-JS-loop (handover §4.A Option B-spawn original):** `fanout-run.cjs` re-implements
    90	loop control-flow in JS (calling runtime pieces as functions/subprocesses per iteration).
    91	Rejected in favour of "invoke the full loop command per lineage" — simpler, reuses the whole
    92	YAML unchanged, no partial reimplementation risk.
    93	
    94	**Option C (agent-orchestrated pool):** Orchestrating agent dispatches all lineages as sub-agents.
    95	Rejected for CLI kinds — they're pooled headless subprocesses; not agent dispatches.
    96	<!-- /ANCHOR:adr-001-alternatives -->
    97	
    98	---
    99	
   100	<!-- ANCHOR:adr-001-consequences -->
   101	### Consequences
   102	
   103	- `fanout-run.cjs` is a pool driver that spawns one CLI subprocess per lineage running the
   104	  full loop. Subprocess command is constructed per `resolveClaudePermissionMode` /
   105	  `resolveCodexSandboxMode` from `executor-config.ts`.
   106	- `step_fanout_spawn_native` in all 4 YAMLs handles native lineages sequentially.
   107	- `step_resolve_artifact_root` in all 4 YAMLs gains a `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir`
   108	  override branch (single-executor path unchanged when the field is absent).
   109	- Native fan-out is NOT pooled — it's sequential agent dispatches. For high parallelism,
   110	  use CLI executor kinds. Native fan-out is appropriate for 1–3 lineages.
   111	<!-- /ANCHOR:adr-001-consequences -->

